  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main purpose of the present study is to verify whether, as compared with
      conventional-intensity noninvasive positive pressure ventilation, high-intensity noninvasive
      positive pressure ventilation may more effective in correcting hypercapnia, hence reducing
      the need for intubation and improving survival in patients with acute exacerbation of chronic
      obstructive pulmonary disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
